N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. tit. 20, ch. I, subch. H - Alcoholic Beverage Tax

State Regulations

Part 60 - Filing Requirements; Returns (§ 60.1 to 60.3)

Part 61 - Records To Be Kept (§ 61.1 to 61.3)

Part 62 - Sales Without Tax (§ 62.1)

Part 63 - Refunds (§ 63.1 to 63.2)

Part 64 - Miscellaneous Provisions (§ 64.1 to 64.5)

Part 65 - Requirement Of Invoices (§ 65.1)

Part 66 - Examples Of Applicability Of The City Tax (§ 66.1)

Part 67 - Repealed

Part 68 - Special Rules For All Distributors Of Liquors And All Transporters Of Liquors (§ 68.1 to 68.5)

Notes
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. tit. 20, ch. I, subch. H
Parts 60 through 68 contained in this Subchapter were
renumbered as part of a reorganization of the department's regulations. These

Parts were previously Parts 315 through 323. The rule making which renumbered
these Parts did not make substantive changes and did not seek to incorporate
intervening changes in the law. The regulations should be read in conjunction
with current law. State regulations are updated quarterly; we currently have two versions available. Below is a
comparison between our most recent version and the prior quarterly release. More comparison features will be added as we have more versions to compare. No prior version found.
